tools: Adds MoveOnCopy to typically move parameters into a lambda.

This is useful in C++11 because it is not possible to capture by move
in a lambda.

Use example:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  // sslContext is move-only.
  auto context = makeMoveOnCopy(std::move(sslContext));
  async_connect([=](ErrorCode e) { // completion handler (captures by value)
    // Get the sslContext back (it has been moved during the copy).
    auto s = createSocket(std::move(*context));
    // ...
  });
  // Beware to not use the context here, since it has been moved inside
  // the lambda.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

